Linux App Ecosystem

A survival guide for Windows refugees on Linux, with a focus on preserving compatibility, muscle memory, and ease of use.
1. Office & Docs

ONLYOFFICE

    The Microsoft Bridge: Opens .docx, .pptx, and .xlsx without destroying formatting.

    Best Compatibility: Offers better compatibility than LibreOffice.

    Clean UI: Features a Ribbon interface that feels like Office 365.

    No Ads: Free desktop and mobile apps.

Scribus

    Professional Publishing: An open-source answer to InDesign.

    Print Ready: Supports CMYK and ICC color management.

    Use Case: Brochures, magazines, and PDFs.

Calibre

    Library Management: Helps manage PDFs, epubs, mobi files, and comic books.

    Functionality: Not just for reading, but also editing, converting, and other utilities.

2. Mail, Calendar & Password Manager

Proton Suite

    Encrypted Lifestyle: End-to-end encrypted email, calendar, and password manager.

    Web-First: Seamless sync across devices, avoiding the hassle of self-hosting.

MailSpring

    Local Desktop Powerhouse: Modern, unified inbox supporting Gmail and Outlook.

KeePassXC

    Password Management: Offline-first manager where you hold the keys.

    Note: The author personally avoids local managers due to syncing hassles, preferring cloud sync solutions.

3. Utilities

KDE Connect

    Seamless Integration: Connects phone and desktop over Wi-Fi.

    Remote Input: Use phone as a trackpad.

    Clipboard: Universal copy-paste across devices.

Btrfs Assistant

    System Recovery Simplified: Benefits from BTRFS disk format to help in recovery.

    Avoids Disaster: Essential for semi-rolling release distros where things might break.

    Note: If you are using Ubuntu or Linux Mint, use Timeshift instead.

Ark

    Archive Manager: Supports zip, tar, 7z, and rar.

    Integrated: Baked right into the Dolphin file manager.

    Fast: Lightweight and simple for quick extractions.

4. Text & Knowledge

Micro

    Terminal Text Editor: Human-friendly editor with standard hotkeys (Ctrl+C/V) in a terminal.

    Mouse Support: Click to move cursor and scroll to scroll.

    No Learning Curve: Easier than Vim and more powerful/simpler than Nano.

Obsidian

    Notes Stack: Markdown-based second brain with graph view.

    Extensible: Has a massive library of plugins.

KWrite

    Quick Editor: KDE-native text editor with instant startup.

    Usage: Comparable to Windows Notepad before recent changes.

5. Creative Tools

Krita

    Digital Painting: Your CorelDraw alternative designed specifically for illustration.

    Brush Engine: Best-in-class tablet support.

Inkscape

    Vector Design: SVG native tool perfect for logos, icons, and diagrams.

    Precision: Powerful node editing tools.

    Alternative to: Adobe Illustrator.

GIMP

    Photo Manipulation: The open-source answer to Photoshop.

    Extensible: Massive library of plugins and completely free.

digiKam

    Photography Workflow: Professional photo management and tagging.

Darktable

    Photography Workflow: Non-destructive RAW editing and color grading.

6. Audio & Video

Audacity

    Audio Editor: Simple, classic waveform editor.

    Use Case: Great for podcasts, voice cleanup, and cutting.

MuseScore

    Music Composition: Professional sheet music creation with realistic instrument preview.

    Alternative to: Sibelius.

LMMS

    Digital Audio Workstation: For beat making and MIDI composition.

    Included: Comes with synths and samples.

    Alternative to: FL Studio.

OBS Studio

    Streaming & Recording: The industry standard for streamers.

    Features: Complex scene composition and low overhead capture.

Blender

    3D Creation Suite: Handles everything from modeling and rigging to animation and rendering.

    Pro Grade: Used in major film and game productions.

Friction

    2D Motion Graphics: Used by Studio Ghibli for vector animation.

    Alternative to: Adobe After Effects.

OpenToonz

    2D Animation: Traditional frame-based animation used by Studio Ghibli.

    Alternative to: Toon Boom.

Kdenlive

    Video Editing: Multi-track professional timeline workflow.

    Performance: Proxy support for smooth editing of 4K footage.

    Alternative to: Premiere Pro.

HandBrake

    Video Transcoder: Compresses video for web or devices with one-click presets.

7. Dev & Infrastructure

Zed

    Editor: High-performance, collaborative editor from the creators of Atom.

Antigravity

    Workflow: AI-first workflows for the modern development landscape.

Cloudflare & VPN

    Web Infrastructure: DNS, CDN, VPN, and security for projects.

    Self-Hosting: Essential for exposing local apps safely.

Podman Desktop

    Container GUI: Secure, rootless containers by default.

    Manager: Handle images, pods, and volumes easily.

    Alternative to: Docker Desktop.

DBeaver

    Database Manager: Universal manager for SQL, PostgreSQL, MySQL, and SQLite.

    Visual: Clean UI for queries and schema visualization.

    Alternative to: DataGrip.

8. Internet & Finance

LibreWolf

    Hardened Browser: Firefox fork with no telemetry.

    Security: uBlock Origin pre-installed.

    Clean: No "pocket" or sponsored shortcuts.

qBittorrent

    File Sharing: Clean interface with no ads or crypto miners.

    Features: Search engine and RSS support built-in.

    Alternative to: uTorrent.

Podcasts

    Media: Gnome podcast client that simply works superb.

KMyMoney

    Finance: Double-entry accounting.

    Identity: The "Quicken" for Linux.
